This paper is primarily focused on face recognition using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the mechanism of face representation in CNNs, which involves the encoding and decoding of neuron responses, indicating a possible connection to neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also proposes a new linear model for face encoding and decoding, which could be of interest to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of parameter space to represent face images, which could be relevant to the neural information processing (cs.NI) sub-category.
